external_knowledge:
- "starter player" refers to a player who is marked as a starter in the `player_metadata` table;
- "top-rated" is determined by the highest average overall rating in the winning matches;
- "winning matches" are matches where the result is 'win'.

- "top-rated players" refers to players with the highest average ratings;
- "2022-2023 season" is the specific time period for the data;
- "more than 10 matches" means the player has participated in at least 11 matches.

- "performance rank" refers to the ranking of a player's performances based on the team rating for each match;
- "top 3 performances" means the three highest-ranked performances for each player;
- "team rating" is a measure of how well the team performed in a match.

- 'Stars' refer to the top two players;
- 'Stepped onto the stage as starters' means players who are marked as starters;
- 'According to their overall ratings' means the players are ranked by their overall ratings, extracted from the JSON ratings data.

- "stars of the match" refers to players who are the man of the match;
- "shine brightly" implies that their ratings are above average (greater than 5);
- "grand arena of competition" is a metaphor for the specific match (match ID = 1).

- 'seasoned warriors' refers to players older than 25 years;
- 'shining stars of the match' refers to players who are the man of the match;
- 'grand arena' refers to the venue named 'StadiumXYZ';
- 'graced the field' means that there are at least two player ratings for the match.

- 'Key players' refers to players who are starters;
- 'High average rating' is defined as an average rating greater than 7.0;
- 'Winning matches' refers to matches where the team's result is 'win'.

- The "dawn of the new year" refers to matches played from January 1, 2022, onwards;
- "Cumulative ratings" are calculated by averaging the overall ratings from the latest ratings for each player;
- "Shining star" and "beacon of excellence" metaphorically refer to the player with the highest average overall rating.

- 'Stars of the game' refers to players who are starters and have played more than 10 games;
- 'Shine with an average overall rating brighter than 5' means having an average overall rating greater than 5;
- 'Graced the field more than 10 times' indicates that the players have played more than 10 games.

- "top 5 stars" refers to the top 5 players with the highest average ratings;
- "constellation of players" is a metaphor for the group of players;
- "shining the brightest" refers to having the highest average ratings;
- "performance ratings" are the ratings given to players for their performance in matches.
